- Context: This page describes the elements of Safe Systems of Work (SSoW) and the requirements for competency, training and awareness.
- Text: 4. Elements of SSoW
The following elements should be incorporated within the Safe System of Work:
•
Systematic approach to planning and design
•
Clearly defined roles and responsibilities
•
Risk assessments
•
Safe work procedures
•
Permit to Work (PTW) systems
•
Control of hazardous energy sources (Lockout Tagout)
•
Emergency preparedness and response
•
Monitoring and review
5. Competency, Training and Awareness
Individuals involved in SSoW should have the necessary competency, training, and
awareness to fulfil their roles effectively. This includes:
•
•
•
•
Understanding the principles of SSoW
Hazard identification and risk assessment techniques
Safe work practices and procedures
Emergency response procedures
