0
Refine documentation based on feedback
0
Ensure compliance and operational alignment
0
Obtain formal approval

8. Key Components of an Effective SSOW
An effective Safe System of Work should include:

8.1 Task Description
Clear definition of the activity and its scope

8.2 Hazard Identification
Identification of all relevant hazards associated with the task

8.3 Risk Assessment
Evaluation of likelihood and severity of harm

8.4 Control Measures
Detailed controls to eliminate or reduce risks

8.5 Roles and Responsibilities
Clear allocation of duties and accountability

8.6 Step-by-Step Methodology
Sequential instructions for carrying out the task safely

8.7 Emergency Arrangements
Procedures for dealing with incidents or failures

8.8 Monitoring and Review
Processes for ensuring continued effectiveness
